    <note type="biography">
        <p>Irish clergyman, mathematician, geologist, and palaeontologist. Professor of geology, Trinity College, Dublin, 1851–81. Became registrar of the medical school after graduating in medicine in 1862. Co-editor of the <hi rend="italic">Natural History Review</hi>, 1854–60. President of the Royal Irish Academy, 1886–91. FRS 1858.</p></note>
